federal funds from
localities that don't cooperate
with U.S.

01:23.283 --> 01:25.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
immigration authorities.

01:25.085 --> 01:29.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The district judge said today
that the president
has no authority to take that
step.

01:29.122 --> 01:35.095 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
His ruling is in effect
nationwide while a
lawsuit against the order is
being heard.

01:35.128 --> 01:39.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The bulls had the run of Wall
Street today,
and the Nasdaq hit a milestone.

01:39.866 --> 01:45.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rally was fueled by strong
earnings at
Caterpillar, McDonald's and
other companies.

01:45.071 --> 01:51.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 232
points to close at 20996.

01:51.411 --> 01:57.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 41 points, to
close above
6000 for the first time ever.

01:57.350 --> 02:00.787 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the S&amp;P 500 added 14.

02:00.820 --> 02:06.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress is back in session, and
raising new
questions about contacts between
Trump advisers

02:06.759 --> 02:08.561 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and the Russians.

02:08.595 --> 02:12.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Leaders of the House Oversight
Committee said
today that former Trump National
Security

02:12.866 --> 02:20.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Adviser Michael Flynn broke the
law by taking
money from Russian organizations
in 2015.

02:20.106 --> 02:23.977 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As a retired general, he was
barred from doing
so.

02:24.010 --> 02:29.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican Chairman Jason
Chaffetz and ranking
Democrat Elijah Cummings spoke
after reviewing

02:29.549 --> 02:30.550 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
classified material.

02:30.583 --> 02:32.352 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:32.385 --> 02:34.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIJAH CUMMINGS (D), Maryland:
There is no
evidence, as the chairman said,
anywhere in

02:34.554 --> 02:38.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
these documents that said he
reported the
funds he received for this trip.

02:38.992 --> 02:46.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is also no evidence that
he sought permission
to obtain these funds from a
foreign source.

02:46.266 --> 02:47.901 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:47.934 --> 02:50.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JASON CHAFFETZ (R), Utah: He was
supposed
to seek permission and receive
permission

02:50.703 --> 02:56.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from both the secretary of state
and the secretary
of the Army prior to traveling
to Russia,

02:56.209 --> 02:59.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to not only accept that payment,
but to engage
in that activity.

02:59.846 --> 03:04.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: An attorney for
Flynn defended
his actions.

03:04.083 --> 03:07.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Representative
Cummings complained
that the White House refused to
hand over

03:07.987 --> 03:10.490 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
relevant documents on Flynn.

03:10.523 --> 03:15.295 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Separately, a Senate
subcommittee announced
that it will hear next month
from former acting

03:15.328 --> 03:19.899 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
U.S. Attorney General Sally
Yates, who played
a role in Flynn's firing.

03:19.933 --> 03:25.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The former Director of National
Intelligence
James Clapper will also testify.

03:25.338 --> 03:30.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia denied again today that
it is arming
Taliban fighters in Afghanistan.

03:30.310 --> 03:36.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is after the top U.S.
commander in Afghanistan
said that he wouldn't refute
such reports.

03:36.783 --> 03:40.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Moscow, Foreign Minister
Sergei Lavrov
dismissed the claims.

03:40.887 --> 03:44.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SERGEI LAVROV, Russian Foreign
Minister (through
translator): As to statements
about alleged

03:44.757 --> 03:49.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
supplies of arms by us to the
Taliban, these
are unprofessional, they are
baseless.

03:49.896 --> 03:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Whatever negative things they
say about Russia
now, simply look into it.

03:54.033 --> 03:57.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No one is providing a single
fact that would
prove such negative statements.

03:57.804 --> 04:03.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Russia has said
that it does
maintain ties with Taliban
officials, but

04:03.476 --> 04:06.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
only to push for peace
negotiations.

04:06.813 --> 04:13.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
North Korea held mass live-fire
exercises
today for the 85th anniversary
of its military,

04:13.519 --> 04:16.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but it didn't carry out a
nuclear test, as
feared.

04:16.956 --> 04:20.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, Pyongyang marked the
occasion with
celebrations.

04:20.526 --> 04:25.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Many people left flowers at the
statues of
the country's former leaders.

04:25.131 --> 04:31.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkish warplanes targeted
Kurdish forces
in Iraq and Syria today, drawing
criticism

04:31.471 --> 04:37.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the U.S. Turkey's military
released video
of the operations, and activists
in Syria

04:37.944 --> 04:40.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
said more than 20 combatants
were killed.

04:40.813 --> 04:46.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most belonged to a Syrian
Kurdish militia
that is fighting the Islamic
State.

04:46.919 --> 04:51.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Turkish officials claimed the
group is linked
to rebels who are battling the
government

04:51.224 --> 04:52.959 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Turkey.

04:52.992 --> 04:59.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The state of Arkansas has
carried out the
nation's first double execution
in 17 years.

04:59.132 --> 05:04.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It happened last night, when two
men were
put to death within three hours.

05:04.237 --> 05:06.072 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham has our report.

05:06.105 --> 05:11.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For 12 years,
the death
chamber at the state prison in
Varner, Arkansas,

05:11.377 --> 05:12.779 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
sat unused.

05:12.812 --> 05:16.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But last night, both Jack Jones
and Marcel
Williams died there.

05:16.849 --> 05:21.854 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both had been on death row for
more than 20
years, both for rape and murder.

05:21.888 --> 05:24.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jones went first, as witnesses
looked on.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID LIPPMAN, Reporter: He
said: "I'm so
sorry.

05:26.092 --> 05:27.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm so genuinely sorry.

05:27.794 --> 05:32.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I hope someday you can learn
more about me
to learn that I'm not a
monster."

05:33.032 --> 05:37.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The daughter
of Jones' victim,
Mary Phillips, had survived the
attack in

05:37.136 --> 05:38.471 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
1995.

05:38.504 --> 05:39.939 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She was just 11 years old.

05:39.972 --> 05:42.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LACY PHILLIPS, Daughter of
Victim: I'm glad
it's done.

05:42.208 --> 05:49.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm glad that part of my life is
-- that chapter
is closed.

05:49.482 --> 05:52.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Lawyers for
Marcel Williams
charged that Jones had been
gulping for air

05:52.685 --> 05:54.153 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as he died.

05:54.187 --> 05:58.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But after a brief delay,
Williams was given
the lethal injection as well.

05:58.291 --> 05:59.992 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He'd expressed remorse last
month.

06:00.026 --> 06:03.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCEL WILLIAMS, Inmate: To
those I hurt,
I'm sorry is not enough.

06:03.396 --> 06:06.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I wish I could take it back, but
I can't.

06:06.966 --> 06:12.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The mother of
Stacy Errickson,
the woman killed by Williams in
1994, said

06:12.538 --> 06:15.007 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he'd finally gotten what he
deserved.

06:15.041 --> 06:18.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Arkansas has now put three men
to death in
the last week.

06:18.711 --> 06:23.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This sudden rush is because one
of the state's
lethal injection drugs,
midazolam, expires

06:23.216 --> 06:27.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at the end of April, and the
drugmakers, citing
concerns over how the drugs were
obtained

06:27.887 --> 06:32.492 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and how they are being used, are
trying to
block the state from getting any
more.

06:32.525 --> 06:34.427 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Governor Asa Hutchinson defended
the process.

06:34.460 --> 06:36.162 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

06:36.195 --> 06:38.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ASA HUTCHINSON (R), Arkansas: I
don't want
to go back to these victims'
families and

06:38.164 --> 06:44.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
say, well, we're worried about
how this looks,
or the speed of this, and so
we're not going

06:44.637 --> 06:49.976 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be able to carry out the will
of the jury
and courts and the sentencing.

06:50.009 --> 06:52.445 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The state
hoped to execute
eight men this month.

06:52.478 --> 06:54.647 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Four have been blocked by
courts.

06:54.680 --> 06:57.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A final execution is set for
Thursday.

06:57.717 --> 06:59.886 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
William Brangham.

06:59.919 --> 07:05.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also today, a
special commission
in Oklahoma recommended a
continued moratorium

07:05.825 --> 07:11.364 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on executions until the system
for carrying
them out is reformed.

07:11.397 --> 07:17.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
