World Health Organization is so
that, when

27:36.021 --> 27:40.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there is a dispute like this, as
there always
will be, it's contained, you
don't get an

27:40.325 --> 27:42.727 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
escalating tit-for-tat spiral.

27:42.761 --> 27:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the real test will be, if
Canada takes
this to a panel with NAFTA or
the WTO, and

27:48.433 --> 27:51.236 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
wins, will the Trump
administration abide
by that ruling?

27:51.269 --> 27:54.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Well, we have
seen a lot
of instances where the president
has talked

27:54.272 --> 27:59.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very tough standing on the
sidelines, and
then, when push comes to shove
and he gets

27:59.811 --> 28:05.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
close with foreign leaders, or
starts these
negotiations, he becomes a
little more conciliatory.

28:05.483 --> 28:08.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's say a trade war or a trade
fight really
does break out.

28:08.887 --> 28:10.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Do you think he will escalate or
de-escalate?

28:10.689 --> 28:13.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG IP: At this point, it's
impossible to
say, and I think it would be
unwise for us

28:13.825 --> 28:16.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to speculate too far, because I
don't think
they really know.

28:16.928 --> 28:20.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think we know this much
about Trump
so far: He believes he's a
deal-maker.

28:20.365 --> 28:21.499 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He likes to bargain.

28:21.533 --> 28:24.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Part of bargaining is that you
talk really
tough.

28:24.169 --> 28:26.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You ask for the moon, you settle
for the topsoil.

28:26.404 --> 28:30.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says -- he beats up on the
Mexicans, he
beats up on the Canadians, but
the point is

28:30.542 --> 28:34.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not to abrogate the treaty and
have the two
of us basically putting up walls
and blocking

28:34.813 --> 28:36.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
trucks at the border.

28:36.181 --> 28:39.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's to come up with a deal that
both sides
feel they can live with.

28:39.384 --> 28:41.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that that's probably
where we're
going to end up.

28:41.953 --> 28:46.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that Trump has people
working for
him who are ultimately
deal-makers.

28:46.157 --> 28:48.093 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the Canadians are the same
way.

28:48.126 --> 28:49.994 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're grownups about this.

28:50.028 --> 28:53.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why you saw the prime
minister of Canada
not respond to Trump with the
same rhetoric,

28:53.865 --> 28:57.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but to talk about the strength
of the relationship
and the desire for a deal.

28:57.168 --> 29:01.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The president
has also said,
as we touched on a little bit,
that he wants

29:01.206 --> 29:02.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to renegotiate NAFTA.

29:02.841 --> 29:04.275 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How would that actually look?

29:04.309 --> 29:05.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How could that unfold?

29:05.877 --> 29:07.645 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What likely might we see?

29:07.679 --> 29:10.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG IP: So, I think one of the
interesting
things is that this dispute did
erupt while

29:10.882 --> 29:13.051 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that renegotiation is under way.

29:13.084 --> 29:16.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Wilbur Ross, taking questions
from the press
today, said he had actually
preferred to have

29:16.221 --> 29:21.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kept those things separate,
because, as we
discussing a minute ago, this
softwood lumber

29:21.259 --> 29:25.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
dispute is a very old dispute
that almost
follows a dynamic entirely of
its own that

29:25.764 --> 29:28.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is actually somewhat independent
of the issues
of the issues that are bothering
the president

29:28.867 --> 29:30.635 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on NAFTA.

29:30.668 --> 29:35.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Unfortunately, because they
could not get
an agreement within the
legislative window,

29:35.373 --> 29:38.209 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it will end up getting sucked
into that agreement.

29:38.243 --> 29:41.446 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's very hard to say
exactly how it turns
out.

29:41.479 --> 29:45.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know from, for example,
drafts that the
administration has circulated on
Capitol Hill,

29:45.817 --> 29:48.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there are a few things they
would like to
change about NAFTA.

29:48.419 --> 29:51.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They would like to, for example,
have the
ability to impose tariffs just
because imports

29:51.923 --> 29:56.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are surging from Canada or
Mexico, not necessarily
because they're being sold
unfairly.

29:56.995 --> 30:02.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They want the ability to not
have -- to be
able to -- they want more
freedom to use our

30:02.267 --> 30:05.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countervailing the subsidy laws
against Canada
and Mexico.

30:05.436 --> 30:09.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Will the Canadians and Mexicans
accept that
as a price worth paying to
preserve the special

30:09.407 --> 30:10.441 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agreement?

30:10.475 --> 30:11.709 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Will they say, no, we'd rather
have no agreement?

30:11.743 --> 30:13.244 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All those things remain to be
seen.

30:13.278 --> 30:19.751 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Greg Ip of The
Wall Street
Journal, thank you very much.

30:19.784 --> 30:25.857 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GREG IP: All right, thank you.

30:25.890 --> 30:33.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: About 65,000
undocumented students
graduate from U.S. high schools
each year.

30:33.398 --> 30:38.970 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Most are protected from
deportation because
of an Obama administration
policy, Deferred

30:39.003 --> 30:44.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Action for Childhood Arrivals,
or DACA, which
allows those brought here
illegally at a young

30:44.742 --> 30:48.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
age to go to school and get work
permits.

30:48.346 --> 30:52.884 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
President Trump tried to
reassure those young
people, often called dreamers,
again this

30:52.917 --> 30:56.221 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
week that he doesn't plan to go
after them.

30:56.254 --> 31:02.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But a lawsuit filed last week
claimed one
dreamer has been deported, and
DACA students

31:02.060 --> 31:03.895 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are on edge.

31:03.928 --> 31:09.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Kavitha
Cardoza of our
partner Education Week traveled
to Los Angeles

31:09.200 --> 31:13.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and spoke to three DACA
recipients to see
how their lives have changed.

31:13.938 --> 31:17.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have agreed to use only their
first or
middle names.

31:17.308 --> 31:21.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is part of our weekly
series on education,
Making the Grade.

31:21.613 --> 31:28.353 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
KAVITHA CARDOZA:
Twenty-five-year-old Jose
has something in common with
President Trump:

31:28.386 --> 31:31.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They both graduated from the
prestigious business
school Wharton.

31:31.923 --> 31:37.729 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Unlike many of his classmates,
Jose didn't
choose a career on Wall Street.

31:37.762 --> 31:43.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE, Undocumented Immigrant:
Teaching sixth
grade math is the most
challenging thing I

31:44.002 --> 31:45.970 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have ever done in my life.

31:46.004 --> 31:48.206 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I wouldn't trade it for the
world.

31:48.239 --> 31:52.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: His students
know he is a
DACA recipient, at a time when
the federal

31:52.510 --> 31:56.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
government is cracking down on
undocumented
immigrants.

31:56.447 --> 32:03.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE: I had a lot of students in
tears asking
me if I was going to be taken
away, and if

32:03.221 --> 32:05.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
they could hide me.

32:05.123 --> 32:09.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I had students asking me, if
their parents
were deported, if they were
going to be allowed

32:09.494 --> 32:13.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to leave with them, or if they
would become
a part of the foster care system
here.

32:13.498 --> 32:19.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Immigration
arrests are up
33 percent nationwide, compared
to the same

32:19.237 --> 32:20.772 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
three months last year.

32:20.805 --> 32:23.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For Jose and others, this adds
to the climate
of fear.

32:23.875 --> 32:27.845 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUDENT: ICE has basically set
up shop at
the Mexican grocery store.

32:27.879 --> 32:29.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they are there throughout
the day.

32:30.014 --> 32:33.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now my mom is like, when we need
to go to
the store or something, we go
out -- we go

32:33.184 --> 32:35.053 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
out at night.

32:35.086 --> 32:46.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STUDENT: It's hard for me to
talk about, because
I know there might be a chance
that, like,

32:46.097 --> 32:47.065 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
my parents can be taken away.

32:47.098 --> 32:49.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that just scares me.

32:49.033 --> 32:49.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE: I tell my students that
they are important,
that their families are
important, that our

32:49.600 --> 32:51.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
community is important.

32:51.402 --> 32:55.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Of the
approximately 11 million
undocumented immigrants in the
U.S., more

32:55.573 --> 32:59.777 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
than 750,000 have been granted
DACA status.

32:59.811 --> 33:06.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To qualify, they would have had
come to the
U.S. as children, be in high
school or graduated,

33:06.417 --> 33:08.453 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with no felony record.

33:08.486 --> 33:11.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Randy Capps is with the
Migration Policy Institute.

33:11.689 --> 33:14.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RANDY CAPPS, Migration Policy
Institute: We
don't usually punish children
for the sins

33:14.592 --> 33:16.294 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of their parents.

33:16.327 --> 33:18.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even if they had crossed the
border illegally,
they didn't know they were doing
it.

33:18.930 --> 33:20.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They were too young to know
that.

33:20.732 --> 33:25.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: He says the
DACA population
has the support of many
Republican, business

33:25.570 --> 33:27.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and university leaders.

33:27.505 --> 33:31.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even President Trump, known for
his tough
talk on the campaign trail:

33:31.409 --> 33:35.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Anyone who has entered the
United States illegally

33:35.413 --> 33:38.049 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is subject to deportation.

33:38.082 --> 33:40.251 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: ... has
softened his stance.

33:40.284 --> 33:42.153 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: We're going to
show great heart.

33:42.186 --> 33:45.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DACA is a very, very difficult
subject for
me, I will tell you.

33:45.923 --> 33:49.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To me, it's one of the most
difficult subjects
that I have, because you have
these incredible

33:49.827 --> 33:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kids, in many cases, not in all
cases -- in
some of the cases, they're
having DACA, and

33:55.166 --> 33:57.835 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're gang members, and
they're drug dealers,
too.

33:57.869 --> 34:01.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But you have some absolutely
incredible kids.

34:01.339 --> 34:03.141 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I would say mostly.

34:03.174 --> 34:06.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Trump's change
in tone has
not been popular with some of
his supporters,

34:06.978 --> 34:10.081 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
like Iowa Representative Steve
King.

34:10.114 --> 34:14.886 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He says he will never be
convinced that the
DACA program makes sense,
because illegal

34:14.919 --> 34:15.887 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is illegal.

34:15.920 --> 34:17.789 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

34:17.822 --> 34:19.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE KING (R), Iowa: If you
reward people
for breaking the law, you get
more lawbreakers.

34:19.757 --> 34:24.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: He says DACA
recipients compete
for jobs with U.S. citizens and
are an economic

34:24.695 --> 34:26.531 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
drain.

34:26.564 --> 34:31.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
According to a 2007
Congressional Budget Office
report, undocumented immigrants
overall do

34:31.602 --> 34:34.472 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
access more services than they
pay in taxes.

34:34.505 --> 34:39.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But DACA recipients, who came to
the states
as children, are mostly
U.S.-educated and

34:39.944 --> 34:43.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
far more likely to move up the
economic ladder.

34:43.214 --> 34:44.682 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
King disagrees, on principle.

34:44.715 --> 34:46.451 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

34:46.484 --> 34:51.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE KING: It's an injustice to
our founding
fathers, to the people who have
fought and

34:51.722 --> 34:57.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bled and died for this freedom
that we have
to simply give it away to people
that have

34:57.728 --> 35:02.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
violated the law, while we have
at least five
million people outside America
that are in

35:02.700 --> 35:06.304 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
line, that do respect our laws,
that are waiting
to come into America.

35:06.337 --> 35:10.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: California has
the highest
number of DACA recipients.

35:10.174 --> 35:12.543 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's also among of the most
welcoming.

35:12.577 --> 35:18.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DACA students here can get state
loans for
college, in-state tuition, and
even a driver's

35:18.049 --> 35:19.851 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
license.

35:19.884 --> 35:23.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yet, this year in California,
financial aid
applications for all
undocumented students

35:23.855 --> 35:29.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were down nearly 60 percent,
because students
feared revealing their status
might put them

35:29.994 --> 35:31.529 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at risk.

35:31.562 --> 35:35.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then a media campaign helped
bring those numbers
up.

35:35.633 --> 35:41.272 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For Yael, a DACA student
receiving financial
aid at UCLA, today's rhetoric
reminds her

35:41.305 --> 35:43.107 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of how she felt in high school.

35:43.141 --> 35:46.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YAEL, Undocumented Immigrant: I
wasn't able
to say I'm undocumented without
just bursting

35:46.511 --> 35:47.879 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into tears.

35:47.912 --> 35:51.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was just, like, painful,
painful and heavy
shame that I felt.

35:51.983 --> 35:55.219 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Yael came to
the U.S. when
she was 4.

35:55.253 --> 35:59.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She volunteers to help other
undocumented
immigrants in her free time.

35:59.257 --> 36:02.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
YAEL: I feel privileged to be
here at UCLA.

36:02.460 --> 36:07.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I think about my future,
unfortunately,
everything seems really
uncertain right now.

36:07.999 --> 36:12.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: For high school
senior Elena,
classes are a refuge.

36:12.370 --> 36:17.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELENA, Undocumented Immigrant: I
motivated
myself to take challenges, like
honors, A.P.

36:17.441 --> 36:19.143 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Classes, extracurricular
activities.

36:19.177 --> 36:22.513 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Elena came here
when she
was 6.

36:22.547 --> 36:25.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She has more than the typical
teenage concerns.

36:25.316 --> 36:30.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELENA: The fear that my parents
might be deported
makes me feel both sad and
scared at the same

36:30.988 --> 36:31.989 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

36:32.023 --> 36:35.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Like, sometimes, going to
school, I'm worried.

36:35.326 --> 36:37.728 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm like, what if I don't see my
mom again?

36:37.762 --> 36:42.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KAVITHA CARDOZA: Elena
volunteers for the
Big Brothers, Big Sisters
program.

36:42.733 --> 36:49.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELENA: When I was a little girl,
I didn't
really have someone to be there
for me, because

36:49.040 --> 36:52.510 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my parents, of course they
didn't understand
the language.

